        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer830729738" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer546230695252118262">This book was not really what I was expecting, which was a practical self-help Buddhist guide to dealing with fear. It felt to me more of an introduction to many different Buddhist concepts with an emphasis on their aspects that address fear and fearlessness but also all of life&apos;s other nasty stuff. <br/><br/>At times the ideas felt opaque, despite Chödrön&apos;s simple, straightforward writing. A lot of the content is presented at a theoretical level with no concrete applications provided. I also found it rep</span>
  <span id="freeText546230695252118262" style="display:none">This book was not really what I was expecting, which was a practical self-help Buddhist guide to dealing with fear. It felt to me more of an introduction to many different Buddhist concepts with an emphasis on their aspects that address fear and fearlessness but also all of life's other nasty stuff. <br /><br />At times the ideas felt opaque, despite Chödrön's simple, straightforward writing. A lot of the content is presented at a theoretical level with no concrete applications provided. I also found it repetitive, but that may just be my feeling overwhelmed with all the new concepts. But sometimes its words inspired me and sometimes I found it profound and thought-provoking.</span>
  <a data-text-id="546230695252118262" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
